{"name": "airthings-ble", "metadata": {"name": "airthings-ble", "version": "0.9.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 2 - Pre-Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Airthings/airthings-ble", "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://airthings-ble.readthedocs.io", "dependencies": ["async-interrupt", "bleak", "bleak-retry-connector"], "summary": "Manage Airthings BLE devices", "upload_time": 1730116100}, "documentation": ["# airthings-ble\n\nLibrary to control Airthings devices through BLE, primarily meant to be used in\nthe [Home Assistant integration](https://www.home-assistant.io/integrations/airthings_ble/). \n\nThe integration supports the following devices:\n\n- [Wave Plus](https://www.airthings.com/en/wave-plus)\n- [Wave Mini](https://www.airthings.com/en/wave-mini)\n- [Wave Radon](https://www.airthings.com/en/wave-radon)\n- Wave Gen 1\n\nAlthough some other devices have BLE capabilities, those devices use BLE for onboarding and configuration.\nIt is not possible to fetch sensor data using this library.\n\n## Getting Started\n\nPrerequisites:\n\n- [Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/) with version 3.11 that is required by Home Assistant ([docs](https://developers.home-assistant.io/docs/development_environment?_highlight=python&_highlight=versi#manual-environment) or [reference](https://github.com/home-assistant/architecture/blob/master/adr/0002-minimum-supported-python-version.md))\n- [Poetry](https://python-poetry.org/docs/#installation)\n\nInstall dependencies:\n\n```bash\npoetry install\n```\n\nRun tests:\n\n```bash\npoetry run pytest\n```\n\nSee [this wiki page](https://github.com/Airthings/airthings-ble/wiki/Testing-with-Home-Assistant) for more details\non how to test the library with HA.\n\n## License\n\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License. See the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details. \n"], "modules": [{"name": "airthings_ble.const", "documentation": ["Constants for Airthings BLE parser"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "airthings_ble.const.MFCT_ID", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.UPDATE_TIMEOUT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_MANUFACTURER_NAME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_SERIAL_NUMBER_STRING", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_MODEL_NUMBER_STRING", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_DEVICE_NAME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_FIRMWARE_REV", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_HARDWARE_REV", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_DATETIME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_TEMPERATURE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_HUMIDITY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_RADON_1DAYAVG", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_RADON_LONG_TERM_AVG", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_ILLUMINANCE_ACCELEROMETER", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_WAVE_PLUS_DATA", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_WAVE_2_DATA", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "airthings_ble.const.CHAR_UUID_WAVEMINI_DATA", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name"